-- National Australia Bank Opens Branches as Computer Problems Delay Payments
-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 2010-11-28T04:12:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/national-australia-bank-posts-2-1-billion-second-half-profit-after-loss.html
National Australia Bank Ltd. , the
nation’s fourth-largest lender by market value, opened some
branches on Sunday to assist customers access funds after
computer problems delayed payments and transactions.  Branches opened in Victoria, New South Wales and Victoria,
the Melbourne-based bank said in a  statement  on its website.  The bank said on Nov. 25 that the processing of some
customer payments and transactions were delayed after “some
issues overnight.” Payments due to be paid into personal
customer accounts on Nov. 26 were also held up while some
scheduled bill payments and transactions using Internet banking
were still to be completed, it said.  “Other delayed payments and transactions will continue to
be progressively processed,” the bank said.  In some instances customers may experience duplicate
transactions and the bank is working as fast as possible to fix
the problem, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Wendy Pugh   in Melbourne 
